&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Looking for something a little different?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Have you thought about working within prison healthcare?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you are looking for a challenging and rewarding Medicines Management Technician role and want to develop your skills in an environment where no two days are the same then this could be the job for you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Medicines Management Technician at HMP Ashfield you will assist in the delivery of a high quality medicines management service to the prison population within a dynamic, friendly team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for dispensing medicines to agreed standards to patients for consumption at medication hatches, as well as issuing patients with their in possession medications to take away, provided by our pharmacy at HMP Bristol. You will also be involved medicines reconciliation and providing pharmacy related information to patients, whilst also counselling of patients on the correct use of medication, reviewing compliance and completing risk assessments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position is a 4 day working week 07:30-18:00 predominantly Monday-Friday with the occasional weekend. You may also be required to cover on occasion annual leave for the staff at our other site - HMP Leyhill in Gloucestershire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please do get in touch to find out more about the role and to arrange an informal visit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Katie Love - Head of Healthcare on 01454 264274 or 07527 292524&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;katie.love@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
